This paper is primarily focused on improving malware detection using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes utilizing file paths as an auxiliary input to the classifier, which is a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The use of neural networks is also mentioned, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses conducting an interpretability analysis, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions using a dataset of approximately 10 million samples, which is a large-scale machine learning task and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
